label: echinoderm anatomy
definition: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

label: anatomical structure
definition: Material anatomical entity that has inherent 3D shape and is generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome

label: anatomical system
definition: A system that has as its parts distinct anatomical structures interconnected by anatomical structures at a lower level of granularity. Multicellular, connected anatomical structure that has multiple organs as parts and whose parts work together to achieve some shared function
exact_synonym: organ system, connected anatomical system, body system

label: whole organism
definition: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of a species and consists of one cell or more

label: anatomical region
definition: A region of the whole organism without well-defined compartmental boundaries

label: embryo
definition: Anatomical entity that comprises the animal in the early stages of growth and differentiation that are characterized by cleavage, the laying down of fundamental tissues, and the formation of primitive organs and organ systems

label: multicellular organism
definition: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of a species and consists of more than one cell

label: digestive system
definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs devoted to the ingestion, digestion, and assimilation of food and the discharge of residual wastes.

label: embryonic digestive system
definition: The gastrointestinal tract that is being formed during embryonic development starting with the formation of the primitive gut tube (or archenteron)

label: larval digestive system
definition: Organ system responsible for the food uptake and processing in the larva

label: adult digestive system
definition: Anatomical system that processes ingested substances in the adult

label: reproductive system
definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with reproduction, i.e. the male and female gonads.

label: embryonic nervous system
definition: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the larval nervous system

label: larval nervous system
definition: The sum of all the neural structures present in the larva

label: endoskeleton
definition: Internal support structure of an animal composed of mineralized tissue. It gives shape, support and protection to the body.

label: water vascular system
definition: The water vascular system is a hydraulic system used by sea urchins for locomotion, food and waste transportation, and respiration. The system is composed of canals connecting numerous tube feet.

label: hemal system
definition: The hemal system contains the blood. It is composed of a complex network of vessels mainly located around the gut.

label: animal hemisphere
definition: Anatomical region that corresponds to the upper half of the embryo, which later is composed of the mesomeres, and ultimately encompasses the presumptive ectoderm
exact_synonym: animal half, upper half, upper hemisphere

label: vegetal hemisphere
definition: Anatomical region that corresponds to the lower half of the embryo, which later is composed of the macromeres and the micromeres, and ultimately encompasses the endoderm and mesoderm
exact_synonym: vegetal half, lower half, lower hemisphere

label: animal cortex
definition: Cell component comprising the outermost layer of the animal region of the oocyte. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins

label: vegetal cortex
definition: Cell component comprising the outermost layer of the vegetal region of the oocyte. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins

label: animal pole
definition: The apical region of the animal hemisphere

label: vegetal pole
definition: The apical most region of the vegetal hemisphere. Once cleavages have started the vegetal pole is characterized by the presence of the micromeres initially and then that of the small micromeres

label: animal pole domain
exact_synonym: apical pole domain, apical plate, animal plate, neurogenic ectoderm, anterior neuroectoderm

label: cell
definition: Anatomical structure that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane

label: cell part
definition: Anatomical structure that is part of a cell and that has a granularity level equal to that of a protein complex or higher.

label: digestive system element
definition: Any of the organs or elements that are part of the digestive system

label: nucleus
definition: A membrane-bounded organelle of in which chromosomes are housed and replicated. In most cells, it contains all of the cell's chromosomes except the organellar chromosomes, and is the site of RNA synthesis and processing. In some specialized cell types, RNA metabolism or DNA replication may be absent

label: germinal vesicle
definition: The enlarged, fluid filled nucleus of a primary oocyte, the development of which is suspended in prophase I of the first meiotic division between embryohood and sexual maturity

label: equatorial pigment band
definition: The subequatorial accumulation of pigment granules (the so-called âpigment bandâ) in eggs or early stage embryos, which constitutes an unambiguous marker of animal-vegetal polarity

label: cytoplasm
definition: All of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures

label: fertilization envelope
definition: A structure that lies outside the plasma membrane and surrounds the egg. The fertilization envelope forms from the vitelline membrane after fertilization as a result of cortical granule release

label: polar body
definition: A small cell formed by the meiotic division of an oocyte

label: spermatozoid head
definition: The part of the late spermatid or spermatozoon that contains the nucleus and acrosome.

label: spermatozoid flagellum
definition: A microtubule-based flagellum (or cilium) that is part of a sperm, a mature male germ cell that develops from a spermatid

label: acrosomal vesicle
definition: An organelle that develops over the anterior half of the head in the spermatozoa

label: oocyte
definition: A female haploid germ cell.

label: mature oocyte
definition: A mature female gamet that has entered meiosis.
exact_synonym: egg, unfertilized egg, female gamete, female germ cell

label: spermatozoid
definition: A mature male germ cell
exact_synonym: sperm, spermatozoa, spermatozoan, male gamete, mature sperm cell

label: blastomere
definition: An undifferentiated cell produced by early cleavages of the fertilized egg (zygote)

label: mesomere
definition: Intermediate size blastomere forming the animal hemisphere of the cleaving embryo

label: macromere
definition: Larger blastomere of the vegetal hemisphere of the cleaving embryo located below the equator

label: micromere
definition: Small blastomere of the vegetal hemisphere of the cleaving embryo located at to the vegetal pole

label: large micromere descendant cell
exact_synonym: large micromere progeny, presumptive PMC, presumptive skeletogenic mesenchyme cell, presumptive primary mesenchyme cell

label: presumptive neuron
definition: A progenitor cell of the nervous system that will develop into a neuron

label: animal pole domain presumptive neuron
exact_synonym: apical pole domain presumptive neuron, animal pole domain neuronal progenitor cell

label: animal quartet
definition: Group of four cells of equal size forming the animal hemisphere of an eight-cell stage embryo

label: vegetal quartet
definition: Group of four cells of equal size forming the vegetal hemisphere of an eight-cell stage embryo

label: vegetal tier 1 upper
exact_synonym: veg1U, veg1 upper, presumptive vegetal ectoderm

label: vegetal tier 2 lower
exact_synonym: veg2L, veg2 lower, presumptive non-skeletogenic mesoderm

label: germ layer
exact_synonym: primary germ layer, embryonic germ layer

label: ectoderm
definition: Primary germ layer that is the outer of the embryo's three germ layers and gives rise to epidermis and neural tissue.

label: larval spicule
definition: A triradiate or hexaradiate minute calcareous skeletal element that initiates most if not all skeletal structures found within the sea urchin embryo, larva and adult.

label: skeletogenic mesoderm
definition: The subset of the mesoderm that will give rise to the skeletal elements.

label: skeletogenic mesenchyme
definition: Skeletogenic mesenchyme is the tissue made up of loosely connected mesoderm cells. It is located in the blastocoel and will produce all of the skeletal elements.

label: syncytium
exact_synonym: multinucleate cell, multinucleated cell, syncytium, syncytial cell

label: skeletogenic mesenchyme syncytium
definition: Anatomical structure composed of skeletogenic mesenchyme cells that have fused to form a single syncytial network.

label: subequatorial skeletogenic mesenchyme ring
exact_synonym: SM ring, subequatorial SM ring, PMC ring, subequatorial PMC ring, primary mesenchyme cell ring, subequatorial primary mesenchyme cell ring

label: ventral skeletogenic mesenchyme chain
definition: Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain on the oral (i.e. ventral) side of the embryo.

label: dorsal skeletogenic mesenchyme chain
definition: Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain on the aboral (i.e. dorsal) side of the embryo.

label: ventrolateral skeletogenic mesenchyme cluster
definition: Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a cluster (i.e. a group of cells) in the ventrolateral region of the embryo.

label: lateral chains of skeletogenic mesenchyme
definition: Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain on either side of the developing digestive tract, along the blastocoel wall and towards the animal pole.

label: right lateral chain of skeletogenic mesenchyme
definition: Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain along the blastocoel wall towards the animal pole on the right side of the embryo.

label: left lateral chain of skeletogenic mesenchyme
definition: Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain along the blastocoel wall towards the animal pole on the left side of the embryo.

label: pigment cell
definition: a cell that contains red coloring matter

label: oral epithelium
exact_synonym: oral epidermis, circumoral epithelium, circumoral ectoderm

label: vestibular pore
definition: Opening located in the left lateral field

label: lateral field
definition: The lateral field is located in the aboral ectoderm of the larva. It separates the anterior and posterior pairs of epaulettes

label: left lateral field
definition: The left lateral field is the lateral field located on the left side of the larva

label: right lateral field
definition: The right lateral field is the lateral field located on the right side of the larva
